						Cornerstone Capital Management Holdings LLC. Decreases Position in Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (APD)					

						 June 27th, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Micah Haroldson 


							Filed Under: Investing - SEC Filing Articles 






Tweet










Cornerstone Capital Management Holdings LLC. cut its stake in  Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (NYSE:APD) by 3.4% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm owned 47,286 shares of the basic materials company’s stock after selling 1,643 shares during the period. Cornerstone Capital Management Holdings LLC.’s holdings in Air Products and Chemicals were worth $6,396,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Other large investors have also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Sullivan Bruyette Speros & Blaney LLC raised its stake in  Air Products and Chemicals by 0.4% in the first quarter. Sullivan Bruyette Speros & Blaney LLC now owns 1,764 shares of the basic materials company’s stock valued at $239,000 after buying an additional 7 shares in the last quarter.  Compton Capital Management Inc. RI raised its stake in  Air Products and Chemicals by 0.5% in the first quarter. Compton Capital Management Inc. RI now owns 1,700 shares of the basic materials company’s stock valued at $230,000 after buying an additional 8 shares in the last quarter.  Hudock Capital Group LLC raised its stake in  Air Products and Chemicals by 0.4% in the first quarter. Hudock Capital Group LLC now owns 2,038 shares of the basic materials company’s stock valued at $275,000 after buying an additional 9 shares in the last quarter.  Bollard Group LLC raised its stake in  Air Products and Chemicals by 0.6% in the first quarter. Bollard Group LLC now owns 2,102 shares of the basic materials company’s stock valued at $284,000 after buying an additional 12 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Bruderman Asset Management LLC raised its stake in  Air Products and Chemicals by 0.4% in the first quarter. Bruderman Asset Management LLC now owns 3,204 shares of the basic materials company’s stock valued at $433,000 after buying an additional 12 shares in the last quarter. 89.65% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 
Shares of Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (NYSE APD) opened at 144.91 on Tuesday. The stock’s 50 day moving average price is $144.56 and its 200 day moving average price is $142.24. The company has a market capitalization of $31.55 billion, a P/E ratio of 10.02 and a beta of 1.25. Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. has a 52-week low of $122.64 and a 52-week high of $150.45. 




Air Products and Chemicals (NYSE:APD) last announced its earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The basic materials company reported $1.43 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $1.38 by $0.05. Air Products and Chemicals had a return on equity of 19.26% and a net margin of 36.19%. The company had revenue of $1.98 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.84 billion. During the same period last year, the business posted $1.82 EPS. The company’s revenue was up 11.4% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, equities research analysts forecast that  Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. will post $6.15 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Monday, August 14th. Stockholders of record on Monday, July 3rd will be issued a $0.95 dividend. The ex-dividend date is Thursday, June 29th. This represents a $3.80 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 2.62%. Air Products and Chemicals’s dividend payout ratio  is currently 26.28%. 
WARNING: This article was originally  reported by Watch List News and is owned by of Watch List News. If you are accessing this article on another publication, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of US & international copyright & trademark law. The original version of this article can be viewed at https://www.watchlistnews.com/cornerstone-capital-management-holdings-llc-decreases-position-in-air-products-and-chemicals-inc-apd/1395892.html. 
Several research firms recently issued reports on APD. BidaskClub lowered shares of Air Products and Chemicals from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a report on Friday. Jefferies Group LLC  reissued a “hold” rating and issued a $155.00 target price on shares of Air Products and Chemicals in a report on Tuesday, May 2nd. Zacks Investment Research lowered shares of Air Products and Chemicals from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Monday, May 1st. Finally, Deutsche Bank AG raised shares of Air Products and Chemicals from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and increased their target price for the stock from $148.00 to $160.00 in a report on Monday, May 1st. Two equities research analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, five have given a hold rating and eight have given a buy rating to the company. The company  has an average rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $153.71.
About Air Products and Chemicals
Air Products and Chemicals, Inc is an industrial gases company. The Company’s Industrial Gases business provides atmospheric and process gases and related equipment to manufacturing markets, including refining and petrochemical, metals, electronics, and food and beverage. The Company operates through seven segments: Industrial Gases-Americas, Industrial Gases-Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA), Industrial Gases-Asia, Industrial Gases-Global, Materials Technologies, Energy-from-Waste, and Corporate and other.
Want to see what other hedge funds are holding APD? Visit HoldingsChannel.com to get the latest 13F filings and insider trades for Air Products and Chemicals, Inc. (NYSE:APD).



